A little too straight this time, this is clipped through square leg for one.
Very solid! Length and on middle, Young gets right behind the line of the ball and defends.
Another one on a length and around middle, defended.
Yet another dot! On middle, Young keeps it out.
Latham once again plays the sweep, it goes through square leg for one.
Fired into the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, blocked.

What a beauty! Wow! Unplayable! All you can do is hope, it misses the outside edge and the off pole. First ball which probably turned from the line of the stumps. It lands on off, Young lunges and looks to defend. This one spins square, past the outside edge and the off pole. This will cause doubts in the batter's mind now. However, it is mostly the balls which slide on that get you and not the ones which turn.
Around middle, defended nicely this time.
Fires this one in on middle, Young plays it off the back foot.
On middle, kept out.
On off, it is pushed to covers.
Makes the batter play yet again by bowling it on middle, Latham negotiates it easily.
Slightly fuller in length and on middle, Latham drives it nicely but finds mid off.
From around the wicket, angles it into the middle pole, Latham plays it back to the bowler. There seems nothing in the wicket for the pacers.
A dot to end! On off, Latham guides it to point.
Fires it on middle, looking for some turn away. This goes on with the arm. Blocked.
Shorter and on off, Young pushes it to covers.
On middle, Young defends it.

NOT OUT! That is missing the leg pole! Did not see that coming! Initially we thought there was bat. Really good decision. This is on middle, Young looks to play the paddle sweep but seems to have missed it. It hits the pad and goes behind. Young is not sure about where the ball is and takes off. It rolls just behind the keeper. Latham asks him to go back and Young does so. He puts in a dive to get in and the throw is also a wide one. The appeal from the Indians in the meantime is turned down. Rahane reviews. Replays show that it is going down with the angle.
On middle, defended.

FOUR! Edgy! Need a little luck on such pitches! Outside off, this one stays low. Young looks to push it through the off side but it goes off the bottom, between the legs of the keeper and down to the third man fence.
Good length and on middle, blocked.
Outside off and fuller, this is driven but to point.
This is well wide outside off, Latham leaves it alone.
Lovely! Angles this in from around the wicket, gets it to land it on off and then move away. Latham looks to drive but is beaten. Trademark Ishant Sharma there.
Outside off, not played at.
On middle, kept out.
Flatter and on middle, defended.
On off, this is pushed to coves.
On the stumps yet again. Young plays it towards point.
Once again makes the batter play, Young easily blocks.
On middle, Young prods forward and plays it back to the bowler.

Slows it up a little and lands it on middle, Young shows the full face of the bat and plays it back to the bowler. Jadeja is accurately hitting the right line and looking for some turn but there are hardly any balls which have misbehaved.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, on off. Latham comes forward and blocks it to mid off.
Length ball, around off. Young pushes it past covers for one. No ball called as the bowler has overstepped.
Short of a length, outside off. Tapped towards the slip cordon.
Short of a length, outside off. Latham works it past mid-wicket for one.
Fuller ball, around off. Young comes forward and blocks it to mid off.
Full ball, on the pads. Young works it towards mid-wicket.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Latham works it back to the bowler.
Shorter ball, around off. Latham blocks it from the back foot.
FOUR! Top shot by Tom Latham! Tossed up, on off. Latham gets low and sweeps it hard to the mid-wicket fence.
Fuller ball, on off. Latham defends it off the front foot.
Loopy ball, on off. Latham blocks it off the front foot.
Shorter ball, outside off. Latham goes back and pushes it to covers.
Shorter ball, around off. Young pushes it to mid on.
Loopy ball, around off. Young blocks it off the front foor.
Nicely tossed up, on off. Young blocks it well.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Young comes down the track and works it to long on for one.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Latham blocks it to the leg side.
Fuller ball, on middle. Young works it towards mid on. But the fielder gets across and cuts it off.
Tossed up, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, around off. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. Young blocks it to the leg side.
Quick single! Full ball, on off. Young drives it towards mid off and takes off for a single.
Loopy ball, on middle and leg. Latham works it to the leg side.
Shorter ball, on off. Pushed to mid on.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Young works it past square leg for one.
Darted on the pads. Worked to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Loopy ball, on the pads. Latham tickles it fine to the fine leg fence.
Full ball, on the pads. Latham works it to deep square leg for one.
Loopy ball, on off. Young blocks it nicely under his eyes.
Latham comes down the track and pushes it to mid-wicket.
Darted on the pads. Worked towards short leg.
Shorter ball, around off. Latham blocks it from the crease.
Loopy ball, outside off. Latham pushes it past cover for one.
Darted on off. Blocked out.
Full ball, on off. Young blocks it off the front foot.
Shorter ball, around off. Latham punches it to cover.
Loopy ball, around off. Latham blocks it out.
Loopy ball, outside off. Latham looks to sweep but the ball  goes just past the off pole.
That has spun sharply! Tossed up, this lands in the rough and turns viciously. Latham looks to drive but gets no bat on it. Rahane dives to his right at first slip and gets his hands to it.
Latham comes forward to block it.
Darted on middle. :Latham works it to the leg side.
FOUR! Great use of the feet! Young dances down the track, gets to the pitch of the ball and drives it past cover for a boundary.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
WOW! Tossed up, on off. Young comes forward to block but the ball turns away and goes past the outside edge and just past the off pole. Patel would like to do that once again.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to cover.
Flatter and on middle. Young blocks it from the crease.
Loopy ball, on off. Young is solid in his defense.
Tossed up, on off. Blocked out.
Flatter and outside off. Latham shuffles across and taps it to cover.
Nicely flighted, outside off. Latham pushes it towards backward point.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out towards the bowler.

Just short of the fielder! Loopy ball, outside off. Latham comes forward to defend but gets the outside edge. The ball lands short of the man at first slip. Some encouraging signs for India in the last few overs.
On the pads and worked past mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Angled into the pads, stays low. Young looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
On middle, defended.
Another one on the stumps, kept out.
That drifts in with the angle from outside off, it is guided to point.
On off, blocked.
Floats it up on off, this is driven back to the bowler who tries to stop it but lets it through. A run taken.
Tossed up on off, blocked.
Floats it up on middle, Young keeps it out with ease.
Another one floated up on off, defended.
On the stumps, Young plays it back to the bowler.
On off, Young plays it to covers.
Flatter and outside off, Young guides it to point.
Half a chance! Down the leg side, Latham flicks it, Saha moves well down the leg side but it hits the glove and goes down to the fine leg region for two.
On middle, defended.
That might have hurt! On off, Latham sweeps, it hits the man at short leg.
On middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
On middle, Young defends it onto the ground.
On the pads, Young sweeps but to square leg.
Well bowled! Sees Latham come down the track and bowls it wide outside off, Latham pushes it to covers.
On middle, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
On off, it is guided to ponit.
On off, this is hit down to long off for one.
On the pads, this is flicked to mid-wicket.
Floats it up on middle, defended.
On the stumps, defended.
On the pads, this is worked to square leg.
On the stumps, defended.
Floats it up on off, kept out.
Beaten! Shorter ball, just outside off. Latham looks to block but the ball turns and goes past the bat.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, on off. Latham pushes it to the bowler.
Nicely tossed up, wide outside off. The turn takes it further away and it is left alone.
Flatter ball, outside off. Left alone.
Tossed up, but wide outside off. Latham leaves this too.
Full ball, on off. Young blocks it under his eyes.
Flat and down the leg side. Young offers his pads.
Full ball, on middle and leg. Young defends it.
Darted on the pads. Young works it past short leg for a single.
That is poor! Full ball, on off. Latham comes down the track and works it to mid on. Yadav misfields and the ball goes through him. Two taken.
Loopy ball, on off. Latham blocks it off the front foot.
Full ball, on the pads. Worked past mid-wicket for one.
Full ball, on off. Latham blocks it back to Ashwin.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Shorter ball, outside off. Latham covers the stumps and leaves it.
Fuller again, on off. Latham blocks it.
A single as this is worked towards square leg.
Latham comes down the track to this one and blocks it.
Fuller ball, just outside off. Latham blocks it out.
Loopy ball, on off. Tom Latham comes down the track and works it to mid-wicket.

FIFTY FOR LATHAM! The experienced southpaw has delivered for the Kiwis! A really good knock by him so far and he has looked unfazed at the crease. He gets there by sweeping this to deep square leg for one.
Flatter ball, around off. It stays low but Young gets hit bat down in time and blocks it out.
Flatter ball, outside off. Left alone.
Flatter and on off, defended.
Outside off, slower, left alone.
On middle, Latham works it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, this is clipped to square leg.

NOT OUT! Nothing on UltraEdge and yet again Latham survives after being given out! The noise was of the bat hitting the pad. This is tossed up around off, it lands and then turns away. Latham looks to defend, does so with his bat close to the pad. There is a noise, Saha takes it and appeals, the finger is raised. Latham reviews but replays show the on-field call has to be overturned.
Floats it up on off, defended.
On off, it is played back to the bowler.
Floats it up on off, this lands and then turns away a touch. Young does well to defend it with soft hands.
Outside off, this is guided to point.
Angled into middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Floats it up on middle, defended.
Another one tossed up on middle, Latham lunges and keeps it out.
Sharma starts with a length ball, quite wide outside off. Young leaves it alone.
Short of a length, but wide again so Young leaves it.
Fuller and closer to the off pole. Young strides forward and taps it towards gully.
Sharma goes full this time and right on the off pole. Young is solid in his defence though.
Short of a length, on off. Young blocks it right from the crease.
Length ball, on the fourth stump. Young puts in a half stride and pushes it to mid off.
Flatter ball, around off. Pushed to covers.
Stays low! Tossed up, outside off. Latham goes to sweep but the ball stays a touch low. Srikar Bharat is not able to gather it and the batters take a bye.
Again, keeps low! Loopy ball, angling across off. It is short so Young goes back to block but he gets the toe end as the ball stays low. The man at first slip gets to his right and stops the ball.
A nice front-foot defence by Young this time.

Short of the fielder! Tossed up, angling across off. Young looks to block but gets the outside edge. The ball drops short of first slip. The fielder dives and gets a hand to it but the ball rolls away. Single.
Loopy ball, wide outside off. Latham looks to paddle it away but gets the inside edge back on the pads. An exciting first over by Ashwin.
FOUR! Through the slip cordon! Full ball, around off. Young goes to punch but gets the outside edge. The ball stays low and goes between second and third slip for a boundary.
Length ball, around off. Wide enough to be left alone.
Full ball, on off. Young comes forward to block it well.
Full this time, on the pads. Young taps it to the leg side.
Short of a length, lands outside off and comes back in a bit. Young shoulders arms to this.
Back of a length again, on that sixth-stump line so Young lets Srikar Bharat collect this one.
Flatter ball, on off. Latham shuffles across and blocks it.
Fuller ball, outside off. Left alone.
Tossed up, wide outside off. Latham sweeps it past square leg for one.
Fuller ball, on off. Young blocks it from the crease.
Very well taken by Srikar Bharat! Loopy ball, lands on off and goes on with the angle. Young is beaten on the defence but Bharat gathers the ball well as it is very, very low.
Young uses the feet and works it past mid-wicket for one.
Full ball, down the leg side. Young misses the flick.
Sharma serves a length ball, outside off. Young gets forward and then leaves it.
Short of a length, outside off. Young toe-ends the pull towards short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Length ball, down the leg side. Young flicks it to the fine leg fence. This is Young's highest score in Test cricket so far.
Full again, on off. Young comes forward and blocks it well.
Length ball, wide outside off. Left alone.
Shorter ball, wide outside off. The ball turns away and keeps very low. Latham looks to sweep but the ball goes under his bat.
Shorter ball, outside off. Punched to covers.
This is way, way outside off. Left alone. Wide called.

Short of first slip! Flatter ball, around off. Latham looks to block but gets the outside edge. The man at first slip dives to his right but the ball drops short of him. It hits the hands and rolls away. Single.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Blocked out.
Young uses his feet and works it to mid-wicket.
Shorter ball, angling across off. Blocked out.
Length ball, lands outside off and comes back in. Latham leaves it.
Fuller this time, wide outside off. Latham comes forward and blocks it to point.
Fuller ball, on off. Latham pushes it towards mid on.
On a length, on the sixth-stump line. Latham pushes it to mid off.
Full ball, outside off. Latham leaves this one alone.
FOUR! Beautiful stroke! A touch fuller again, outside off. Latham puts in a stride, offers the full face of the bat and the ball races to the cover fence.
FOUR! Excellent use of the feet! Tossed up, on leg. Young gets to the pitch of the ball and lifts it wide of mid on for a boundary. That brings up the 150 for New Zealand.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Blocked out.
Darted down the leg side. Left alone.
Loopy ball, outside off. Young gets forward and blocks it.
Flatter and on the pads. Worked to mid-wicket.
Fuller, on off. Clipped to the leg side.
Length ball, around off. Latham gets forward to block it.
Play and a miss! Length ball, a bit wider outside off. Latham looks to drive it away but gets beaten.
On a length, outside off. Latham blocks it well.
Good-length ball, on the sixth stump. Left alone.
Full again, but angling across off as Sharma goes over the wicket. Latham leaves this one too.
Length ball, tempting Latham to go for the drive but the southpaw leaves it yet again.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! The stand finally ends and Ravichandran Ashwin is the one to provide with the breakthrough! Fuller again, outside off. Young tentatively looks to block it but fails. Srikar Bharat gathers the ball behind the stumps and the fielders start celebrating. The umpire is unmoved but Bharat is convinced and convinces Rahane to go upstairs. A big spike on UltraEdge as the ball goes past the bat and Young's vigil stay ends!
Howout: c sub Srikar Bharat b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: Loopy ball, around off. Kane Williamson gets hit on the pads and the ball goes to leg gully.
Flatter ball, on off. Pushed to the bowler.
Tossed up, on middle. Kane Williamson looks to block but gets the inside edge past short leg.
Fuller ball, on middle and leg. Blocked out.
Williamson uses his feet and taps it to mid on for a single. He is off the mark.
On a length, on off. Williamson taps it to the off side.

Full ball, on the pads. Kane Williamson works it past mid-wicket. Two fielders chase it and keep it to three. Well, actually make that four as the umpire calls it a no ball for overstepping. So, three runs off the bat and one extra.
Length ball, outside off. Latham leaves it alone.
On a length, around off. Latham pushes it to mid off.
Full ball, around off. Latham gets forward and blocks it.
Short of a length, outside off. Latham taps it down on the pitch.
FOUR! Very good shot by Latham! Short of a length, outside off. Latham goes back and punches it past cover for a boundary.
Play and a miss! Tossed up, angling across off. Kane Williamson gets low and looks to slog sweep it but misses. Bharat fails to gather and the batters get a bye.
Loopy ball, on off. Latham taps it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, around off. Latham blocks it off the front foot.
Fuller ball, around off. Latham pushes it to covers.
Darted on the pads. Latham taps it to the leg side.
Nicely tossed up, wide outside off. Latham lets the keeper collect it.
Fuller ball, on the pads. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, around off. Kane Williamson blocks it off the front foot.
Full ball, outside off. Tapped down on the pitch.
Shorter ball, around off. Pushed to covers.
Fired full and outside off. Kane Williamson leaves it alone.
Loopy ball, on off. Kane Williamson comes forward and blocks it.
Flatter ball, outside off. Left alone.
FOUR! Swept and swept well! Tossed up, down the leg side. Latham gets low and sweeps it behind deep square leg for a boundary.
Loopy ball, outside off. Left alone.
Tossed up, around leg. Blocked out.
Flatter ball, on off. Tom Latham blocks it from the crease.
Darted on middle. Latham gets the inside edge past short leg.
Flatter and on middle, Williamson lunges and blocks.
Darts is on the stumps, this time the length is slightly shorter. Defended.
Floats it up on off this time, slightly slower. Blocked.
FOUR! Nicely played! Kane Williamson stays back, the length is shorter and there is also room. He finds the gap between point and covers. Boundary.
Corrects his line and length! This is on off and flatter. Blocked.

FOUR! Towards the left of the cover fielder this time. Second in the over. Short again and outside off, Williamson hangs back and pushes it through covers. Finds the gap and once you do that, you need not run on this lightning fast outfield.
Angled into the pads, Latham works it through square leg for one.
Floats it up and on middle, defended.
That is a beauty! A loopy delivery, at almost 81 MPH. It dips, lands and turns away from off. Latham looks to defend but misses.

Another loud appeal but turned down! Probably pitching outside leg or missing off. Two balls in a row that haven't turned quite a lot. This lands around leg and then spins square. Latham looks to defend but is beaten by the turn. It hits Latham on the back leg. A huge appeal but turned down. Replays show that it did pitch in line but maybe it spun too much. Well, well! Ball Tracker shows three reds. Had India reviewed this, Latham would have been out!
Slower through the air but the line is well outside off, left alone.

A single to end, this time he darts it in, on the pads, Latham works it through square leg for one. End of a testing over by Ashwin. Did get the ball to turn a couple of times. This could be good signs to come for India.
Skips down the track but does not get to the pitch of it. Defended.

FOUR! Just past the leg slip fielder! It went very fine, Pujara had no chance! He though probably seems too square and that is what Jadeja tells him. This lands on middle and then turns in. Latham looks to flick but it goes more off the inner half and down to the fine leg fence.
Comes down the track but the length is shortened yet again, this is worked through square leg for one.
Floats it up on middle, Williamson prods forward and blocks.
On off, shorter, this is pushed through covers for one.
A dot to end! On middle, blocked.
Flatter and on off, Williamson pushes it towards cover and wants one but is sent back.
Soft hands! On the pads, Williamson tucks it to the man at leg slip.
Another one nicely tossed up and on off, blocked.
Yet another one which is floated up and on middle, Kane looks to work it on the leg side. It goes off a soft leading edge back towards the bowler.
A little too full this time, KW strokes it wide of mid off for one.
Another one tossed up and on off, Latham is solid in defense.

That has almost shaved the off pole. Fires it on off and then this turns away just a little. Williamson can't do a lot about it, he tries to block the original trajectory. Is beaten and the ball just about kisses the off pole.
This one now goes on with the arm, on middle, Williamson blocks.

Went fetching after that one. Lands just short. This is slightly slower and around off, turns away. Williamson ends up playing it away from the body with soft hands through. It goes off the outside edge but lands short of the widish slip fielder.
On middle, blocked.
Slightly shorter and on the pads, this is flicked to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Williamson pushes it through covers and gets to the other end. No maiden then.
Slower but down the leg side, turns away further. Left alone.
Flatter and on off, Williamson hangs back and defends.
On middle, Williamson works it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, Williamson flicks it to mid-wicket but does not find the gap again.
That is a beauty! The carom ball, it lands on middle and then turns away. Williamson looks to defend but is beaten. Ball doing quite a lot now.
A dot to end! On the pads, Williamson flicks again but this time can't beat short leg. A maiden by Ashwin.
On off, blocked.
On middle, defended.
Flatter and on middle, it is kept out.
Another one on the stumps, defended.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Another one on the stumps, Latham negotiates it easily.
Another one floated up on off, blocked.
Angled into the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.

Once again that has turned square! Flighted ball, lands on off and then spins away quite a lot. Goes past the outside edge as Latham tries to defend. A little more fuller and that will be causing more problems. This is short enough for the ball to turn past the outside edge.
Gives it flight but bowls it outside off, left alone.
On middle, defended nicely.
Safe! Ashwin has started causing problems here. Luck not going his way but. Slower and it lands on the pads, Latham looks to flick but it goes off the leading edge, lands well short of cover.
Slightly slower and on off, blocked.
Flatter and on off, Williamson goes back and defends.
This one keeps low! Angled into the pads, Williamson looks to flick, it goes more off the inner half down to fine leg for one.
Latham once again uses his feet but does not get to the pitch of the ball. Defended.
This time he gets closer to the pitch of the ball, pushes it to mid on and gets to the other end.
On off, defended.
Fires it into the stumps. Blocked.
Fuller, this is worked to mid on for a quick run. Gill was on his heels there.
Fires it on middle, Williamson defends.
Attacks the stumps again, kept out.
On the off pole, Williamson lunges and manages to play it towards the off side.
Jadeja continues to bowl it on the stumps. It is kept out nicely.
The batters probably did not go for a run as it was Jadeja! Latham comes down the track and works it to mid on. He takes off but then opts not to go for it.
On off, Latham keeps it out.
Yet another ball on middle, Latham works it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! Just over! Latham does take the risk and it comes off! He comes down the track again, gets a little too close to the ball. Latham whips it, hits it well enough to clear Jadeja at mid on. Boundary.
On middle, Latham stays in his crease and defends.
Another one on the stumps, Latham keeps it out with ease.
Williamson comes down the track but pushes it back to the bowler.
Another one tossed up on off, defended.
Floats it up on off, Kane pushes it to covers.
Darts it onto middle from wide of the crease, kept out.
On middle, Williamson negotiates it safely.
This one comes in with the arm, slightly shorter. Williamson hangs back and blocks.
Good length and outside off, left alone.
On off, this is pushed to mid off.
Another one on off, Latham lunges and defends.
FOUR! Nicely played! Shorter and outside off, Latham uses the pace and guides it past gully for a boundary.
This one is now angling away from the off pole, left alone.
On middle, defended. So just the boundary from the over.
Flatter and outside off, Williamson leaves it alone. A little more zip on that delivery. New ball so quite understandable.
Yet again, quicker and on off, zips through. Williamson guides it to point.
This one comes in with the arm and on off, defended.

Was that a chance? No! The angle almost does Williamson in. This is quite wide outside off, now because of the around the wicket angle, Williamson is worried about the ball angling in. He ends up hanging his bat out away from the body. It goes off the outside half but lands short of Agarwal who is in a very close-in gully type position. It is more of a silly point actually.
Down the leg side, Williamson looks to flick but misses.
Safe! No short leg and Williamson escapes! This one angles into middle, Williamson looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge, onto the pads, lobs on the leg side for one.
Shot! No runs but! Shorter and outside off, it is guided to point.
On middle, defended.

OUT! THREE REDS AND INDIA STRIKE AT THE STROKE OF LUNCH! Big, big wicket and the second new ball has worked. Also, to get a pacer on from one end has proved to be a good idea. Umesh Yadav runs in, lands it around off and gets it to jag back in. Williamson is glued to his crease as he tries to put bat on ball. Misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal and the finger is raised. Williamson reviews. Time for the replays and Ball Tracker shows three reds. New Zealand lose a review. Also, this will really lift the morale of the Indian side. Lunch will now taste a lot better as the players make their way off the field.
On a length, around off. Taylor blocks it with ease.
FOUR! Off the mark with a boundary! Full ball, down the leg side. Taylor flicks it well. The man at short mid-wicket dives but cannot get to the ball. Boundary.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out to the bowler.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Latham comes down the track and blocks this one.
Shorter ball, around leg. Latham comes down the track and works it past short leg for one.
Fuller ball, on the pads. Flicked to the leg side.
Darted on the pads. Taylor clips it past leg gully and gets a single.
A dot as Latham comes down the track to block this one.
Length ball, around off. Pushed to mid on.
Length ball, on the pads. Taylor works it to deep square leg and picks up a single.
On a length, but wide enough for Latham to leave it.
Short of a length, around off. Latham gets the inner half back on the deck while looking to block.
Shorter ball, outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, angling on the pads. Latham works it towards deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Taylor blocks.
Taylor comes down the track and blocks this one.
Coming in with the angle from outside off. Taylor defends with ease.
Fuller again, just outside off. Ross Taylor gets forward to block it.

Stumping missed! Darted on the leg stump. Taylor looks to work it away after getting down the track. But the ball goes through his legs. Srikar Bharat is blinded by Taylor and has no idea where the ball is headed. It hits his pads and goes to the leg side. A bye is taken. Actually, the replay shows that Taylor got an inside edge on it. Which is why the ball went further away from Bharat. So, it will be a run.
Tossed up, around off. Latham reaches to the pitch of the ball and blocks it.
Short of a length, outside off. Chopped away towards point.
Nicely done! Full ball, on off. Taylor nicely pushes it down the ground. Ashwin chases it from mid on and keeps it to two.
Short ball, down the leg side. Taylor ducks under it.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
This stays low! Short ball, on off. Taylor looks to duck under it but the ball does not rise much. It is right to his helmet as he is crouching a bit. He blocks it right in front of his helmet.
On a length, around off. Taylor gets the outside edge towards point.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Fuller ball, outside off. Latham gets his head over the ball and blocks it.
Quicker on the pads. Worked past square leg for one.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
On the pads, Taylor works it towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up, around off. Taylor pushes it to mid off.
On a length, but wide enough. Latham gets forward and then leaves it.
Short of a length, lands outside off and angles in. But Latham covers the stumps and leaves it.
Full ball, on the fifth stump. Latham covers the stumps and pushes it to cover.
Yet another solid front-foot defence by Latham.
On a length, angling in from outside off. Latham taps it back towards Yadav.
Shorter and wider outside off. Latham guides it to deep cover for a single.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Tapped to the leg side.
Tossed up, wide outside off. Latham gets down the track and pushes it past covers for one.
Flatter ball, just outside off. Taylor blocks it with soft hands.
Brilliant by Jadeja! Fuller ball and Taylor dives it to the left of mid off. Jadeja runs across and dives to stop it. One taken.
Darted around middle and leg. Latham plays it to the leg side.
Loopy ball, around off. Latham gets forward and blocks it to the off side.
Short of a length, around off. Taylor pushes it back to the bowler.
Length ball, on off. Taylor pushes it towards mid off and sets off for a single.
Fuller ball, wider this time. Latham gets forward and pushes it straight towards cover.
Short of a length, on the fourth stump. Latham goes back and blocks it.
Fuller this time, on off. Pushed to mid on. They look for a single but decide against it.
Length ball, on the pads. Latham clips it straight towards mid-wicket.
Darted on the pads. Taylor looks to work it to the leg side but gets hit on the pads. A soft appeal for LBW.
Shorter ball, outside off. Chopped to covers.

OUT! TAKEN! A sharp catch by the keeper! Tossed up, on off. Taylor looks to block but the ball turns just enough to take the outside off. Srikar Bharat takes a good catch to his right. He makes up for the missed opportunity a few overs ago. This wicket would put India in a pretty good position.
Howout: c sub Srikar Bharat b Axar Patel

Commentary: Loopy ball, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up, outside off. Nicholls comes forward to block but gets the inside edge towards short leg.
Shorter ball, outside off. Nicholls runs it towards third man for one.

Straightaway makes the left-hander uncomfortable! Tosses it up, it lands on middle. Nicholls is unsure whether to come forward or to stay back. In the end, he just tries to put bat on ball, it goes off the outer half to point.
Flatter and on the pads, this is worked to square leg for one.
Shorter and outside off, Latham pushes it to covers.
Another one tossed up on off, Tom lunges and keeps it out.
On the pads, Latham flicks it through mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Gives it air, lands it on middle, Henry Nicholls puts in a good stride forward and keeps it out.
Flatter and on off, this is pushed back to the bowler.
Angled into the pads, Latham works it through square leg and takes one.
On middle, blocked.
Close! This lands outside off and then turns back in. Nicholls lunges to defend but does so outside the line, it goes off the inner half but wide of short leg.

OUT! IMPACT IS UMPIRE'S CALL! What Nicholls thought could save him does not. New Zealand lose another and all of a sudden they are in a spot of bother. They still trail by over 120 runs. One brings two for Axar Patel! This is fuller and it lands on off and turns back in. Nicholls looks to sweep but misses. He gets hit on the pads. A huge appeal and the finger is raised. Nicholls probably feels he has got hit outside the line of off and reviews. Replays roll in and they show the on-field call stays. New Zealand do not lose a review but they do lose a batter. Nicholls does not trouble the scorers a lot.
Close! This is angled into middle, goes on with the angle. Blundell looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads.

Just wide! All of a sudden, things are happening here. This lands on off and then turns away. Latham looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge past the gully fielder and down towards third man for three.
Slows it up, it lands on leg and goes down leg. Left alone.
Loopy ball and on middle, defended.
A full toss on the pads, this is worked towards long on for one.
Tosses it up on off, Latham pushes it to covers.
Floats it up on off, Latham defends.
On middle, defended.
Angled into middle, goes on with the angle. Blocked nicely.
A little too straight, Blundell with soft hands, works it down towards fine leg for three.
Quick run! On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket. They take off. The fielder gets to the ball and fires a throw which is just wide than the keeper would have liked. The batter makes it in.
On off, blocked.
Flatter and on middle, Blundell is solid in defense.
Slows it up and bowls it well outside off, left alone.
Slightly shorter and on off, it is pushed to covers.
On middle, blocked.
A huge appeal from the man behind the wicket but Ashwin has no interest. Indicates an inside edge. Tossed up on off, Latham looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On off, defended.
Slightly shorter and on off, Latham guides it to point.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, around off. Tom Blundell blocks it off the front foot.
Full ball, outside off. Tom Blundell gets forward and pushes it to cover.
Darted on the pads. Worked to the leg side.
Shorter ball, outside off. Tom Blundell goes back and pushes it to cover.
Angled in from outside off. Tom Blundell is solid in his defence.
Shorter ball, down the leg side. Flicked past square leg for one.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Tom Blundell taps it to the leg side.
Fuller and on leg. Worked to short leg.
Flighted delivery, on off. Tom Blundell blocks it.
Full ball, on off. Pushed back towards the bowler.
Ashwin bowls it full and on the pads. Blundell taps it towards mid-wicket.

OUT! STUMPED! A marathon knock by Latham comes to an end! Tossed up, outside off. Tom Latham comes down the track to drive but gets the inside edge. The ball goes back to the keeper and Srikar Bharat does the rest. The TV umpire is called in to check whether he collected the ball ahead of the stumps but he did not!
Howout: st Srikar Bharat b Axar Patel

Commentary: Loopy ball, around off. Pushed past cover for one.
Darted on the stumps. Tom Blundell works it towards square leg.
Loopy ball, on off. Pushed to covers.
Fuller ball, on off. Defended out.
Full and on the stumps. Tom Blundell blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up, on off. Ravindra blocks it off the front foot.
Fired around off. Ravindra offers the full face of the bat.
Tossed up, wide outside off. Left alone.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Flighted ball, around off. Ravindra gets it from the toe end towards first slip.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full ball, on off. Tom gets on the front foot and blocks it.
Quicker ball, around middle and leg. Tom Blundell works it towards short leg.
Shorter ball, outside off. Punched towards cover.
A bit more flight on this one, on off. Tom Blundell blocks it off the front foot.
Full ball, on off. Tom gets the inside edge towards leg gully.
On the pads. Tom Blundell works it towards square leg.
Bowled on the pads, Rachin kicks it away.

FOUR! Beautifully played. Very classy! Overpitched on off, Rachin Ravindra strokes it down the ground. Yadav at deepish mid off, runs to his left and dives but does so over the ball. Boundary. Exquisite timing.
Flatter and on middle, from around the wicket now. Defended.
Another one floated up on off, kept out nicely.
Loopy ball and on off, defended.
Flighted, this lands and turns away. Rachin Ravindra opens the face of the bat at the very end and guides it towards point.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed to covers.
Fires it on off, Tom lunges forward and keeps it out.
On off again, blocked.
Slightly fuller this time, Blundell pushes it to covers.
Fires it on the stumps, Tom leans forward and plays it back to the bowler.
A quick maiden then from Jadeja! On middle, Tom lunges and defends.
Angled into the pads, this is pushed towards mid on for one.

A huge appeal but it is probably turning too much! This lands on off and then spins back in sharply. Blundell looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. He also loses his balance and is out of his crease. As the bowler is appealing, the keeper gets to the ball and tries to back-flick it onto the stumps but misses. The appeal is also turned down. Tom Blundell probably would have been in had the keeper hit the stumps. Ball Tracker shows the ball to be missing.
Flatter and on middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball and on off, blocked.
Flighted and on off, defended.
Another nicely tossed-up ball on off, Tom Blundell keeps it out with ease.
Good running! On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
Angled into the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Unplayable! This lands on off, it comes in with the angle, lands and then turns away. Blundell is beaten as he tries to block.
On middle, Blundell keeps it out again.
Fires it on off, Tom is solid in defense.
Another defensive stroke to this ball on off.
Shorter and outside off, Rachin Ravindra quickly moves onto the back foot and pushes it through covers for two.
On the pads, this is worked to square leg.
Lovely stuff! Gives it air, this drifts in, lands around off and then turns away. Whizzes past the outside edge of Rachin Ravindra's bat as he tries to defend.
On middle, defended.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Nicely timed! On the pads, RR hangs back and works it through square leg. This one races away to the fence.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, around off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, around off. Tom Blundell pushes it to cover for one.
Flatter ball, on off. Ravindra blocks it from the crease.

OUT! BOWLED! Ravindra gets Ravindra! Through the gate! Tossed up, wide outside off. This lands in the rough and turns back in sharply. Rachin Ravindra gets forward to block but Ravindra Jadeja gets the ball to go through the gate and onto the stumps!
Loopy ball, on off. Pushed to covers.
Darted on middle. Kyle Jamieson gets forward and blocks it.
Loopy ball, around off. Tom comes down the track and blocks it.
Flatter ball, on off. Tom Blundell gets the outside edge towards slip but on the bounce.
Darted on the pads. Blundell works it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Loopy ball, outside off. Kylie taps it to the off side.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Beautifully bowled! This lands on off and goes on with the angle. Kyle Jamieson looks to block but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Loopy ball, around off. Blocked out.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to deep cover for one.
Shorter ball, outside off. Punched to covers.
Full ball, on off. Kyle Jamieson pushes it back to the bowler.
Fired in on middle. Kyle Jamieson gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it.
Full ball, on off. Jamieson blocks it from the crease.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out. No ball called as Ishant Sharma has overstepped.

NOT OUT! Length ball, lands outside off and comes back in a bit. Tom Blundell looks to flick it but gets hit on the pads. There is a big appeal by Sharma but the umpire is unmoved. Sharma convinces Rahane to take the review at the last moment. But Ball Tracker shows that the ball is sliding down the leg stump!
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Full ball, on the pads. Worked to mid on.
On a length, wide outside off. Tom prods forward and leaves it.
Sharma serves a length ball, outside off. Tom covers the stumps and leaves it.
Length ball, on off. Tom blocks it to the off side.
Full ball, on off. Pushed down the ground. Jadeja dives to his left and gets his hand to it.
On off. Kyle Jamieson works it to mid on.
Tossed up, around off. Pushed to cover.
Shorter ball, on off. Kyle Jamieson goes back and blocks it.
Shorter ball, outside off. Punched to covers.
Full ball, on off. Kyle Jamieson looks to drive but gets the inside edge on the pads.
Length ball, outside off. Tapped to silly mid on.
This lands outside off and comes back in a bit. Tom leaves it though.
Short of a length, on off. Tom Blundell looks to pull but gets hit on the body.
Length ball, on the pads. Worked to the leg side.
Full ball, on the pads. Worked past mid on for one.
Short of a length, outside off. Kyle Jamieson works it towards seond slip.
Loopy ball, on off. Tom gets forward and blocks it.
Full again, on off. Tom blocks it right under his eyes.
Darted on the pads. Tom Blundell blocks it straight down the pitch.
Full again, on middle. Blocked out.
Fired in on the pad. Tom Blundell taps it to the leg side.
Fuller and outside off. Tom Blundell works it behind backward point for one.
On a length, around off. Tom Blundell gets forward and blocks it.
Full and on the pads. Tom works it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Short of a length, outside off. Pushed to covers.
Length ball, on the pads. Kyle Jamieson works it to deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Length ball, on the pads. Flicked in the air by Kyle Jamieson but it lands just short of square leg.
Length ball, on off. Pushed to covers. That is Tea on Day 3!
Flatter and on middle, defended.
Another one is fired on middle, Blundell keeps it out nicely.
Slightly slower and on off, Blundell guides it to point.
Another one quicker and on middle, kept out.
Floats it up on off, Tom pushes it to covers.
Plays this one with the angle to the fielder at mid-wicket. A maiden to begin with.
Fired into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Quicker and on middle, Kyle Jamieson pushes it to covers. A single taken. 250 up for the Kiwis.
Slightly shorter yet again, looking to push it through. Defended.
Fired on the pads, Tom looks to flick but misses. Half an appeal but turned down.
Better! Slows it up a touch and lands it on off, slightly fuller. Defended.
Just the single from this one! On off, Blundell looks to drop and run but no run there.
On the shorter side yet again, this is defended off the back foot.
Angled into the pads, Kyle Jamieson works it through square leg. Takes two.
On off, this is pushed to covers.

Better! On off, slightly fuller, this one turns away a touch. Kyle looks to push, it goes off the outer half towards backward point for one. There could have been a second as Yadav fumbled but the batters opted against it.
Goes wide of the crease and darts it on off, defended.
Floats it up this time a touch, on off, blocked.
Just short! Outside off, shorter. Kyle looks to cut, there is extra bounce, it goes off the top edge but lands short of point.
Shorter and on middle, Kyle Jamieson hangs back and keeps it out.
On off, this is pushed through covers for one.
Fired on middle, defended.
Another one on the stumps, Blundell defends it onto the ground.
Slightly fuller and on off, Tom squeezes it out towards point.
On off, this is played to point.
On middle, defended.

That could have been a chance! On middle, Kyle Jamieson looks to defend, it goes off the inner half towards square leg. They go for one, it is a risky single but the fumble from the fielder makes it easy.
On off, blocked.
Outside off, this is pushed through covers for one.
A dot to end! On off, defended.
Flatter and on off, this is pushed to covers.
Blundell steps down the track but does not get to the pitch of it. Defended.

Two! Good effort by Mayank but he concedes the extra run! Outside off, this is played towards point. Agarwal there dives to his right but he pushes it away from the fielder backing up. An extra run taken.

OUT! TIMBER! That is unplayable! Probably Tom Blundell could have played ahead to that delivery but can't really blame him, it just never got up. Flatter and on middle, Blundell hangs back and tries to defend, this one does not bounce at all. It sneaks under the bat and hits the stumps. Axar has hit 4th. Blundell was playing really well but can't do a lot with that delivery. The stand which was frustrating India has been broken. New Zealand still trail by 87. Tim Southee is the next batter.
On off, tossed up, this is pushed to covers.
On middle, defended.
On off, fuller, this is pushed down to long off for one.
On middle, defended.
Another one on the stumps, kept out with ease.
On middle, Southee works it to mid-wicket.
Another one on off, this is pushed to covers.
Shortish and on off, this is played to covers.
Angled into middle from wide of the crease. Blocked.
Slightly shorter and on off, this is pushed to mid off.
FOUR! Up and over! This is fuller, tossed up on middle, it is lofted over the mid on fielder for a boundary. The tall man uses his reach there.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed to covers.
This is fuller and on off, it is hit hard but Yadav at deepish mid off runs to his right and keeps it down to one.
Floats it up on off, blocked.
On middle, Kyle defends it.
Flatter and on the stumps, it is pushed to mid off.
Floats it up on off, Kyle Jamieson strokes it to covers.
Angled into the pads, this is played to the man at mid on.
Fuller and on off, Kyle Jamieson pushes it down to long off and gets to the other end.
Another single to end! On off, this is eased to long off for one.
Flatter ball, outside off. Pushed to covers.
Full ball, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
FOUR! Tossed up, wide outside off. Tim Southee dances down the track and heaves it past mid on for a boundary.
OUT! BOWLED! Patel gets yet another 5-fer! Flatter ball, on off. Southee goes back to block it but the ball turns away a touch and castles the stumps! William Somerville walks out to bat.
Shorter ball, outside off. Cut away to point.
Flatter ball, on off. William Somerville blocks it from the crease.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to mid off.
Shorter ball, outside off. Kane Williamson stays back and blocks it.
Nicely driven but towards short cover.
Full ball, on off. Pushed to short cover.
Loopy ball, on off. Kyle Jamieson gets forward and blocks it.
Beaten! Tossed up, lands on off and turns away sharply. Kyle Jamieson looks to block but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Full ball, on leg. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. Blocked out.
Fuller ball, around off. Pushed to cover.
Tossed up, around off. William Somerville comes forward and blocks it.
Shorter ball, on middle and leg. Blocked out.
Another solid block to end the over.
Shorter ball, outside off. Punched to covers.
Loopy ball, on off. Kyle Jamieson comes forward and blocks it.
A single as this is pushed to long off.
Tossed up, outside off. William Somerville comes to the ball and blocks it.
Shorter ball, outside off. Pushed towards point.
Tossed up, on off. William Somerville comes on the front foot and blocks it.
Short of a length, outside off. Punched to deep cover for one.
Flatter ball, on middle and leg. William Somerville goes back and blocks it.

FOUR BYES! Sharp turn! Full ball, lands on off and turns away sharply. William Somerville comes forward to block but the ball goes past the outside edge. The keeper cannot collect it and the ball runs to the fence.
Shorter ball, outside off. Pushed to point.
Flatter ball, on off. Pushed to covers.
Tossed up, wide outside off. William Somerville leaves it alone.
Shorter ball, on off. Punched to long on for one.
Loopy ball, around off. William Somerville pushes it past cover for one.
Shorter ball, outside off. Kyle Jamieson punches it to long off for one.
Loopy ball, outside off. Left alone.
Nicely tossed up, on middle and leg. William Somerville plays it back to the bowler.
Flighted again, outside off. Pushed to cover.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed back to Patel.
Darted on the pads. Kyle Jamieson looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.
Tossed up, outside off. Kyle Jamieson looks to block but gets no bat on it.
Loopy ball, on off. Pushed to short cover.
Shorter ball, on off. Pushed to mid on.
Shorter ball, outside off. Kyle Jamieson punches it to long off for one.
Loopy ball, around off. Kyle Jamieson comes forward and blocks it.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to mid on.
Flatter ball, on the pads. Worked to deep square leg for one.
Loopy ball, around off. William Somerville comes forward and blocks it.
Slower through the air. Outside off pushed to covers.
Loopy ball, on off. William Somerville taps it to cover.
Flatter ball, outside off. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. Kyle Jamieson works it to mid-wicket.
A single as this is worked to long off.
Full ball, on off. William Somerville goes back and blocks it.
Just past the off pole! Patel bowls it shorter, on off. William Somerville looks to block but the ball turns and goes past the off pole.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to cover.
Tossed up, on off. Kyle Jamieson punches it down the ground. Ashwin dives to his right but gets no hand on it. Single.
Darted on the pads. Worked to the leg side.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to cover.
Darted on the pads. William Somerville looks to block but gets hit on the pads. The man at short leg takes it and appeals but there is no bat on it.
Flatter ball, on off. Pushed to cover.
Tossed up, on the pads. William Somerville looks to flick but the ball flicks his pads. The keeper and the man at leg slip fail to gather. A leg bye is taken.
Darted on the pads. Worked past square leg for one.
Loopy ball, around off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, outside off. William Somerville blocks it off his front foot.
A solid off the front foot by William Somerville.
Flatter ball, wide outside off. William Somerville leaves it.
Full again, on off. Pushed to cover.
Shorter ball, on off. Kyle Jamieson works it to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball, outside off. Blocked out.
Shorter ball, on off. Pushed to mid on.
Full and on the pads. Kyle Jamieson flicks it to the leg side.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.

OUT! TAKEN! The vigilant stay of Kyle Jamieson ends! Ashwin tosses this nicely, outside off. Kyle Jamieson goes for the slog sweep but gets more height than distance on it. The ball goes towards deep mid-wicket and Axar Patel takes it. Ajaz Patel is the last batter.
Howout: c Axar Patel b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: Length ball, around off. Pushed past point for one.
Full ball, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Short of a length, down the leg side. William Somerville works it to deep square leg for one.
Shorter ball, outside off. Patel pulls it to square leg.
On a length, on off. Patel blocks it from the crease.

FOUR! In the gap! Short ball, on the body. Patel pulls it away in the air. There are fielders at deep mid-wicket and deep square leg. They converge but the ball lands between them and runs to the fence.
Flatter ball, lands on off and turns back in. The ball clips the pads of William Somerville and Srikar Bharat fails to gather it. The ball goes to fine leg and they take two leg byes.
Full ball, on off. Pushed to covers.
Tossed up, around off. William Somerville drives but straight to cover.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Just a single as this is pushed to long on.
Flatter ball, on middle. Ajaz Patel defends it with his bat and pad together.
Full toss, on the pads. William Somerville flicks it away. The ball goes to the left of deep mid-wicket. Ravichandran Ashwin dives and keeps it to a couple of runs.
Short of a length, outside off. Pushed to cover.
Full ball, on off. William Somerville drives it towards mid off.
Short of a length, outside off. Punched to cover.
Short ball, on the body. William Somerville works it to deep square leg for one.
Yorker, just outside off. Patel blocks it out.
Full ball, on the pads. Worked to the leg side.
Loopy ball, on middle and leg. William Somerville comes forward and blocks it.
OUT! BOWLED! That ends the innings! Tossed up, on middle. William Somerville goes for the sweep but gets no bat on it. The ball goes onto hit the stumps. New Zealand are bowled out for 296!
India and Agarwal are underway! The lead also touches 50. Around off, shapes away. Agarwal looks to defend, this goes off the outer half through point for one.
Another one on a length and around off, Gill guides it to point.
Gill is off the mark too! Fuller and on off, this is driven through covers for one.
Another one on a length and around off, blocked.
BEATEN! That is a beauty! Length and on off, angles in at first but lands and leaves the batter. Agarwal is squared up as he tries to block. Gets beaten.
Outside off, Agarwal guides it to point.

OUT! TIMBER! 50th Test wicket for Kyle Jamieson! He just continues to impress. Strikes on the very first ball, just the start his side wanted. The half centurion of the first innings falls for just a single run. Kyle Jamieson is also the fastest to 50 wickets in Tests for the Kiwis. Right on the money from the word go. Length and on off, jags back in a touch. Gill probably should be coming forward on a wicket that is not bouncing a lot. His feet though are glued to the crease. He looks to defend it half-heartedly. It sneaks past the bat, clips the pad and hits the stumps. Kyle Jamieson is delighted. There is still time for another wicket.
The outswinger to welcome Pujara! Slightly fuller and on off, shaping away. Defended.

This one stays low! That spot, there is a spot outside off where if the ball lands, tends to stay low. Kyle Jamieson probably landed it there. It does not get up. Pujara is beaten as he tries to block.
On middle, defended.
On off, blocked.

FOUR! Can be called a fortunate boundary! Pujara, right at the end, decided to play that shot. Short and on middle, he intially looks to duck under it but then realises that it is not bouncing a lot. He then opens the face of the bat at the very end, goes between gully and the slip fielder for a boundary.
Good length and on off, Agarwal defends it.
Just outside off, left alone.
Good length and on off, Agarwal blocks it out.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, Agarwal shoulders arms to this one.
On middle, Agarwal works it to mid on.
Outside off, left alone.

Almost another one! That inswinger is causing problems! Length and outside off, this lands and jags back in. Pujara looks to defend but leaves a gap between bat and pad. It sneaks through and just goes past the off pole.
Back of a length and on off, blocked.
Length and on off again, it is kept out nicely.
Fuller and on middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
EDGY FOUR! Soft hands! On off, shapes away. Pujara leans forward and tries to defend, this goes off the outside edge through point for a boundary.
Fuller and on middle, this is pushed to mid on.

Very close! Flight, it starts outside off and then drifts back in. Agarwal initially looks to drive but the realizes he is not going to get to the pitch of the ball. He looks to defend, this goes off the inside edge past the off pole and down to the fine leg region for two.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg, they run the first one quickly but settle for it.
On middle, blocked.
Pujara comes down the track, Patel bowls it short. Defended.
Pujara skips down the track, makes it into a low full toss and whips it wide of mid on for one.
Kyle starts with a full one, down the leg side. Pujara goes for the flick but misses.
FOUR! Easy pickings! First runs of the day! Length ball, down the leg side. Pujara clips it nicely to the fine leg fence.
Again. Length ball, on the pads. Clipped to deep square leg for one.
On a length, around off. Mayank taps it towards cover.
FOUR! Through the slips! On a length, drawing Mayank Agarwal forward to block. The ball takes the outside edge but runs between first slip and gully and runs to the fence.
Short of a length, around off. Blocked out. 9 from the first over.
Full and down the leg side. Pujara misses the flick.
Full and on the pads. Pujara clips it well. The man at square leg dives but over the ball. It is cut off by deep backward square leg. Two runs.
Full ball, on off. Pujara gets forward and blocks it.
Full ball, on off. Pujara blocks it with ease.
Full again, on middle and off. Pushed towards mid on.
Short of a length, on off. Pujara pushes it back to the bowler.
Kyle Jamieson fires a full one, on the pads. Mayank Agarwal looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls away and a leg bye is taken.
Length ball, around off. Cheteshwar Pujara comes forward and blocks it.
Short of a length, around off. Worked to mid-wicket.
Short of a length, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara cuts it well but the man at point stops it.
Full and on the pads. Clipped away and the man at square leg dives over it. Two taken.

Better line and length! Probably the first time that Kyle Jamieson has bowled the perfect delivery this morning. Short of a length, just outside off. Pujara looks to block from the crease but there is a bit of extra bounce and it takes the outside edge. The man at first slip dives to his right but it drops short of him.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full and on the pads. Pujara works it past square leg for one.
Full and on the pads again. Clipped away nicely but the man at square leg dives to his right and stops it.
On a length, around off. Blocked out.
Short of a length, just outside off. Mayank Agarwal covers the stumps and then leaves it.
Fuller and wider outside off. Agarwal leaves it with ease.
Full and on the pads. Pujara works it to the right of square leg for one.
Length ball, on the sixth stump. Mayank Agarwal puts in a nice stride and pushes it to point.
Short of a length, lands outside off and comes back in. But it is left alone by Mayank Agarwal.
Fuller and closer to the off pole. Mayank Agarwal blocks it.
Length ball, just outside off. Pushed to cover.
Back of a length this time, outside off. Agarwal pushes it to covers from the crease.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Pujara works it past mid-wicket for one.
Stays very low! Shorter ball, outside off. Mayank Agarwal goes for the pull but stays very, very low. The keeper does well to gather it.
Darted down the leg side. Left alone.
Loopy ball, on off. Mayank Agarwal gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it.
Full ball, on off. Pushed to cover.
Flatter ball, on off. Mayank Agarwal goes back and blocks it.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Kyle Jamieson strikes early! Short ball, down the leg side. Cheteshwar Pujara looks to leave it alone. Tom Blundell gathers it and is up in arms and so is Kyle Jamieson. But the umpire is unmoved. The keeper and bowler convince Kane Williamson to take the review. There is a spike on UltraEdge as the ball passes the gloves! Pujara has to walk back now.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Kyle Jamieson

Commentary: Length ball, outside off. Left alone.

Well bowled! Full ball, lands on off and comes back in. Rahane is stuck in the crease while looking to block. The ball goes onto hit the pads and there is an appeal for LBW but it is turned down. Good decision as Ball Tracker shows that the ball is going over the stumps.
Short of a length, outside off. Rahane looks to cut it away but the ball bounces a bit more than usual and goes past the outside edge.
Low full toss, on off. Pushed to mid off.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Flatter ball, on off. Mayank Agarwal goes back and blocks it.
FOUR! Punished! Short ball, down the leg side. Mayank Agarwal pulls it nicely to the square leg fence.
Fuller this time, on middle. Mayank Agarwal goes back and deals with the low bounce to block it.
Well bowled! Tossed up, on middle. Mayank Agarwal gets to the ball to block but gets the outside edge. It drops short of first slip though.
Darted on the pads. Mayank Agarwal looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to cover.
On a length, outside off. Rahane gets forward and then leaves it with ease.
Short of a length, outside off. Rahane rides the bounce and taps it to the off side.
Length ball, around off. Blocked out.
BEATEN! On a length, just outside off. Rahane has his feet glued to the crease and looks to poke at it. The ball shapes away a bit and goes past the outside edge.
Short of a length, outside off. Punched to point but the fielder dives and stops the ball.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out by Rahane.
Darted on the pads. Agarwal gets the inside edge towards deep square leg for one.
Loopy ball, on off. Rahane gets forward and taps it out.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Rahane looks to work it to the leg side but gets hit on the pads.
FOUR! Lovely stroke! Full ball, on off. Rahane nicely drives it to the cover fence.

OUT! LBW! PLUMB IN FRONT! Tossed up, lands on off and comes in with the angle. Rahane plays for the turn and looks to block. The ball hits his pad right in front of the stumps and the finger goes up. Rahane has a word with Agarwal but decides not to review it. That looked dead straight, to be honest. Rahane's poor run of form continues.
Loopy ball, on leg. Iyer blocks it out with ease.
Short of a length, on off. Blocked out.
Short of a length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal punches it to point but the fielder dives and stops it.
Length ball, on off. Mayank Agarwal gets his head on top of the ball and blocks it.
Kyle Jamieson bends his back and bowls a short one, on off. Mayank ducks under it.
Full and way outside off. Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone.
Short of a length, lands outside off and shapes away. Left alone.
Darted on the pads. Iyer works it past square leg for one.
Flatter ball, on off. It stays low but Mayank Agarwal gets his bat down in time and blocks it.
FOUR! Tossed up, on off. Mayank Agarwal comes down the track and takes it on the full. He hits it over mid off and slips and falls on the pitch. The ball runs to the fence.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, wide outside off. Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone.
Full ball, around off. Agarwal gets forward and blocks it.
FOUR! THROUGH THE SLIPS! Length ball, around off. Iyer looks to block but gets the outside edge. The man at first slip is quite wide. The ball goes between him and the keeper to run to the fence.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Beaten! Full ball, lands on off and shapes away. Iyer comes forward and looks to block but the ball goes past the bat.
A single as this is pushed to mid off.

Beautiful bowling! Southee pushes the ball from wide of the crease. It comes in with that angle, lands outside off. Mayank Agarwal looks to block it from the crease but it shapes away and goes past the outside edge.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Flatter and on middle, defended.
Slows it up and lands it on middle, Iyer lunges and defends.
Slower yet again, lands it on middle, gets it to dip. Iyer strokes it back to the bowler.
Slightly shorter this time and on off, Iyer pushes it to covers.
Angled into the pads, Iyer works it to mid-wicket.
A maiden then by Patel! On off, loopy delivery, played towards cover.
Good length and on off, blocked.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Number 4 down and Southee gets his first! The morning session keeps getting better for the visitors. Southee has his 50th Test wicket against India. What a delivery! How skillful is this guy! The last delivery, landed on a similar length but then, it went on with the angle, Agarwal played a forward defensive stroke and it hit the middle. This time, it lands on a similar area, that is on a length and around off, moves away after pitching. Agarwal looks to do the same, he tries to play the original trajectory. The movement does him in though, it goes off the outside edge to the man at second slip. Latham makes no mistake.
Howout: c Tom Latham b Tim Southee

Commentary: Outside off, left alone.

OUT! LBW! Three reds and Jadeja has to walk back! Not sure why he took the review there. That was plumb if there was no bat. Southee has two in the over and India have their backs against the walls now. They are effectively 100 for 5. Well, they could be 100 for 6 as we don't know if Wriddhiman Saha is going to bat. The swing proves to be the undoing of an Indian batter again. Southee goes full, gets it to tail back in nicely from outside off. Jadeja plants his front foot way too across, he then tries to flick but misses. It hits the back pad. Southee is celebrating as he appeals. The finger is raised. After a chat with Iyer, Jadeja reviews. To no avail though. He takes a review along with him.
Length ball, down the leg side. Ashwin looks to flick but gets no bat on it.
A double-wicket maiden for Southee! Fuller and on off, swinging away. It is driven to covers.
Down the leg side, Iyer looks to flick but misses.
Floats it up on middle, blocked.
Close! Iyer comes down the track but ends up yorking himself. He jams it out to covers.
Slips another one down the leg side, Iyer looks to flick but misses.
On middle, kept out nicely.

FOUR! That is a poor ball! Especially with the pressure building, that is a delivery which released a little bit of pressure. It is very short and very wide outside off, Iyer guides it past short third man for a boundary.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! This is more of a confident shot. Not a lot wrong with the delivery, length and on middle, Ashwin pushes it past mid on. Races away to the fence.
Two more! Ashwin proving there are not many demons in this wicket. Length yet again and on off, this is driven on the up, through covers for two.
Really good batting! Length and outside off, Ashwin opens the face of the bat and guides it through point. One taken.
Length and on middle, extra bounce. Iyer takes one hand off the handle as he blocks.
FOUR! All of a sudden runs flowing now, momentum seems to be shifting again. On the pads, Iyer works it fine and this one races away to the fine leg fence.
Goes wide of the crease and bowls it well wide outside off, left alone. 11 from the over.
On off, this is pushed to mid off for one.
Slower, Iyer strokes it towards sweeper cover for one.
Angled into the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Slightly slower but shorter, Ashwin pushes it to covers.
FOUR! Cut away! Ashwin has crossed the 10-run mark in no time! Shorter and outside off, Ashwin cuts it through point for a boundary.
Now uses his feet but does not get to the pitch of the ball. Defended.
Fuller and outside off, swinging away further. Left alone.
That is a beauty! Fuller, inviting the batter to drive. Iyer does look to do so but this one shapes away at the end, whizzes past the outside edge.
Fuller and on middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On off, kept out nicely.
Outside off yet again, not played at.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the off pole, this is guided through point for one.
On middle, defended.
Loopy ball on off, blocked nicely.
The arm ball, it lands on middle and then goes on with the angle, Iyer looks to defend but it goes off the inner half on the leg side.
Yet another one on the stumps, kept out.
Well bowled! Slower through the air, lands it on off and gets it to hold its line. Iyer looks to defend, it goes off the outer half to point.
On off, blocked.
On middle, defended nicely.
Angled into the middle pole, Ashwin stands tall and plays it to mid on.
Outside off, this is guided through point for one.
Uppish but well short! On middle, Iyer looks to play it to mid on, ends up doing so a little ahead of his body, goes uppishly but lands short of mid on.
Fuller and on off, Iyer pushes it to mid off.
Another length ball outside off, Iyer leaves it alone.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, kept out.
Fires it into the pads, defended.
Flatter and quicker but on the pads, Ashwin looks to flick but misses.
Good fielding but can't stop the single! Outside off, this is guided to point. The fielder dives to his right and makes a half stop.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Shorter and on off, Ashwin stands tall and defends it onto the ground.
Fuller and on off, this is driven nicely but to mid off.
Goes wide of the crease and bowls a bumper, a good one, Ashwin is taken by surprise, he tries to pull but is late on it.
Good length and on middle, extra bounce. Ashwin does well to defend it with soft hands.
FOUR! Fortunate boundary! Fuller and on off, shaping away. Ashwin looks to drive, this goes off the outside edge down to the third man fence.
Looks to guide it past gully again but this time he hits it on the bounce to the fielder there.
On middle, defended.
Attacks the stumps again, kept out with ease.
Loopy ball on off, Iyer pushes it wide of mid off for one.
On middle, slower through the air, it is pushed to covers.
Very short and on middle, Ashwin works it through mid-wicket for two.
On off, Ashwin pushes it to cover.
Shorter and on middle, this is pushed through mid-wicket for one.
Flatter and on off, Ashwin hangs back and defends.
On middle, this is worked to square leg.
Another one on the stumps, it is worked to square leg.
Slower through the air and on middle, Ashwin keeps it out.
Shortish and on off, Ashwin pushes it to covers.
Outside off, Iyer looks to guide it down to third man but it goes off the underedge towards the man at first slip.
Once again, he opens the face to this delivery outside off. The fielder at first slip moves to his right and stops it.
Loopy ball on middle, defended nicely.
Fires in a full toss now, it is pushed to the bowler.
On middle, Iyer lunges and keeps it out.
Slower through the air, it lands on off and spins away. Iyer looks to drive but it goes off the outer half to covers.
This one is down the leg side, left alone.
On middle, Ashwin defends it.
Fuller and outside off, Ashwin looks to drive, he gets beaten. The ball stays low, hits the pad of the keeper and goes behind. A run taken. Bye.
On middle, defended.
On the pads, Iyer works it to mid-wicket.
Down the leg side, a waste of a delivery. Iyer kicks it away. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 4!
Loopy ball, around off. Pushed to covers.
Tossed up, outside off. Ashwin looks to drive but gets the outer half of the bat towards short third man.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Top shot! A bit short and a touch outside off. Ashwin rocks back and cuts it behind backward point for a boundary.
He cuts it again but straight towards backward point.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Edged again! Length ball, around off. Iyer gets half a stride to block but gets the outside edge. The ball goes between second and fourth slip for a boundary.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Iyer gets hit on the pads and the ball rolls away to the leg side. He got some bat on it so it is given as runs.
Full ball, on off. Ashwin nicely punches it down the ground. The man from mid off runs to his right and dives to stop it. Single.
Length ball, on off. Pushed to mid on.
On a length, on middle. Iyer works it to mid on.
On a length, on off. Iyer taps it to covers for one.
Tossed up, on off. Iyer drives it well but Latham at short cover dives to his left and gets his hands to it.
Tossed up, on off. Iyer taps it down on the deck.
Shorter ball, around off. Punched to covers.
Nicely tossed up, on off. Shreyas Iyer blocks it off the front foot.
Another dot as this is pushed back to the bowler.
On off, defended.
FOUR! Nicely done! Short ball, outside off. Ashwin drags it past mid-wicket. Kyle Jamieson chases it from mid on but loses the race.
Play and a miss! Length ball, outside off. Ashwin goes at it with his hands but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Length ball, on off. Pushed to mid off.
Short again, on middle. Ashwin pulls it to deep square leg for one. 100 up for India.
On a length, on off. Iyer stays in the crease and blocks it.
Length ball, on off. Pushed to mid off with ease.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Blocked out.
Tossed up, around off. Ravichandran Ashwin taps it back to the bowler.
Darted on the pads. Clipped to the leg side.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to covers.
Flatter ball, on off. Ashwin goes back and blocks it.
Loopy ball, on leg. Ashwin looks to flick it but the ball turns and hits him on the pads.
Length ball, on off. Iyer taps it towards mid on for one.
Length ball, around off. Ashwin gets forward and blocks it out.
Short ball, on middle. Pulled away to deep square leg for one.
Full ball, on off. Iyer gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it.
Short of a length, on off. Iyer stays in his crease and blocks it.
Wider outside off. Southee tempts Iyer to drive but the latter leaves it.
Flatter ball, on off. Ashwin goes back and blocks it.
Shorter ball, on off. Ashwin goes back, covers the turn and blocks it.
Loopy ball, outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin comes forward and blocks it.
Darted on middle. Ashwin blocks it out.
Arm ball, on off. Ashwin gets forward and blocks it.
Ashwin gets to the pitch of the ball and works it to long on for one.
On a length, around off. Ashwin taps it towards slip.

OUT! BOWLED! The stand ends and Kyle Jamieson is the man to provide with the wicket! Short of a length, outside off. Ashwin has his feet glued to the crease and looks to punch it away. But all he gets is the inside edge which goes back on the pads and then rolls back onto the stumps! The move to bring back Kyle Jamieson works well for New Zealand. But Rachin Ravindra and Tim Southee should also get the credit for the way they kept things tight. Wriddhiman Saha walks out to bat.
Short ball, outside off. Left alone.
Short of a length, outside off. Saha lets the keeper collect it.
Play and a miss! Fuller and closer to the off pole. Saha pokes at it tentatively but gets beaten.
Short of a length, outside off. Tapped to covers.
Flatter ball, around off. Iyer chops it towards short third man for one.
Loopy ball, outside off. Saha opens the face of the bat and plays it past short third man. Young chases it and slides to keep it to three.
Flatter ball, on off. Punched to covers.
Loopy ball, around off. Tapped to point.
Shorter ball, on off. Shreyas Iyer plays it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, on off. Iyer blocks it down on the deck.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out by Saha.
Fuller ball, around off. Saha pushes it to cover.
Kyle Jamieson lands it on a length, outside off and gets it to come back in. Saha though covers his stumps and leaves it.
Full ball, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller again, wider outside off. Saha drives it well but the man at covers dives and stops it.
Short of a length, outside off. Saha rides the bounce and taps it out.
FOUR! Quality stroke! Flatter and quicker, outside off. Iyer goes back and then late cuts it past short third man for a boundary.
Loopy ball, around middle and leg. Blocked out.
Flighted ball, around off. Shreyas Iyer gets forward and blocks it.
Full ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. Iyer taps it to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball, on middle. Iyer plays it back to the bowler.
Short of a length, on leg. Saha works it past square leg for one.
Length ball, on middle. Iyer pushes it to mid on.
Full and on the pads. Iyer flicks it past mid-wicket. The man in the deep runs to his left and stops it. Two taken.
Length and on the pads. Iyer works it top deep square leg for one.
Full again, on off. Saha pushes it to the off side.
Short of a length, wide outside off. Saha leaves it alone.
Loopy ball, on off. Worked down to long on for one.
Flatter ball, around off. Saha blocks it out.
Shorter ball, outside off. Saha taps it past backward point and picks up a couple of runs.
Flatter ball, on the pads. Blocked out.
Tossed up, outside off. Saha comes forward and blocks it.
Low full toss, on off. Pushed down to long on for one.
On a length, around off. Saha taps it down on the deck.
Back of a length, on off. Saha goes back and blocks it.
Short ball, on off. Saha looks to leave it but gets hit on the body. The ball rolls to the left of the keeper, who dives and stops it.
Well bowled! Length ball, lands outside off and comes back in. Saha gets forward to defend it but the ball sneaks through the gate and he is hit on the pads.
Short of a length, outside off. Saha leaves it alone.
Short ball, on off. Saha ducks under it.
BEATEN! Fractionally short and outside off, this one skids through. Iyer looks to push it through the off side but misses.
Tosses it up on middle, this is worked down to long on for one.
Gives it air and lands it on off, blocked.
A little flatter this time, on middle, Saha hangs back and defends it onto the ground.
Just outside off, Saha shoulders arms to this one.
The sweep comes out, he though hits it towards the fielder at square leg.
Flatter and on middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Floats it up on middle, kept out.
Got his bat down in time! This is on middle, Iyer shapes to cut, realizes the ball is coming in, he manages to play it to point.
Tossed up on middle, defended.
Floated up on off, blocked.
Slower through the air and lands it on off, defended nicely.
Tosses it up on middle, defended.
On middle, defended.
Another one, floated up on off, Saha lunges and keeps it out.

FOUR! Just over! Some agression from Saha! He steps down the track, does not get to the pitch of it but drags it, it goes uppishly but over mid-wicket for a boundary. It was actually a chance, it went straight through the hands of Henry Nicholls. A drop. Could prove very costly.
SIX! That is nailed! Saha has probably decided to step on the accelerator here. He goes down on one knee and slog-sweeps it over the mid-wicket fence.
On middle, Saha lunges and keeps it out. A really good over for India.
Steps out but gets too close to the pitch of the ball, it is hit down to long on for one.
Loopy ball on off, defended.
Flatter and outside off, Saha leaves it alone.
Another one on middle, blocked.
Attacks the stumps again, this is played back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on off, Saha leans forward and keeps it out.
Floats it up on off, it is pushed to covers.
Shorter and on middle, this is pushed down to long on for one.
Floats it up on middle, Saha defends.
On off, this is pushed to mid off.
On middle, it is worked to square leg.
Fires it on middle, Saha plays it back to the bowler.
SIX! Over the fence! That is as straight as an arrow! Iyer steps down the track and lofts it down over the bowler's head for a biggie. He is into the 40s now.
On off, defended.
Very full and outside off, it is jammed out to point for one.
Floats it up on off, blocked.
Yet another tossed up ball on off, kept out again.
A low full toss on the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
A single as this is eased down to long on.
On the pads, Iyer leaves it alone and lets it hit his pad.
Shorter and on middle, Iyer goes back and blocks it.
Another one tossed up on middle, it is eased down to long on for one.

TWO BYES! That does not bounce at all! Shorter and down the leg side, turns and also stays very low. Saha looks to pull but misses. The keeper fails to collect it cleanly as he is slow to get down. Two taken.
Just over this time! On middle, Saha whips it just over the leaping fielder at mid-wicket. There is a man in the deep so only one.
On the pads, it is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Shorter and on the pads, Iyer flicks it through square leg and gets to the other end.
Floated up on middle, it is kept out.
Gives it air and lands it on off, Saha defends it onto the ground.
Outside off, left alone.
Down the leg side, Saha lets it go to the keeper.
On the stumps, defended.
Fuller and on middle, this is flicked but the man at mid-wicket dives to his left and stops it.
Outside off, Iyer guides it through short third man for two.
Floats it up on off, it is played back to the bowler.
